snippet.textDisplay: I can't say for sure that Liverpool are the best team in the world. They are definitely among the best teams in the world. Who like me is tired of Steve Nicol's Liverpool bias. The man tried to defend the Liverpool youngsters after they were clobbered 5 - 0 by Aston Villa. Who does that? He talks trash about other clubs yet he sees positives in a game where Liverpool loses by 5 goals. Many will agree with me Liverpool were just lucky to win the champions league period. Remember when Chelsea won it back in 2012? They went past Barcelona. They won against Bayern Munich in the final. Luck plays a big part in these games. Liverpool have been getting favourable draws period. Look at how lucky Liverpool were in the last UCL draw, they are to play Atletico Madrid while Manchester City will battle Real Madrid. I feel if Liverpool were to play Barcelona over a 5 game series they will lose. You know I am right. The best team should be rated by consistency not a once off game which anyone can win. Not a hater, just saying.  GG - MANCHESTER UNITED
